        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 7:04PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles east of Virginia Dale to near
Pennock Pass, or extending from 31 miles north of Fort Collins to 24
miles west of Fort Collins, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Collins, northwestern Loveland, Windsor, Wellington, Timnath,
Stove Prairie, Pennock Pass, Teds Place, Bellvue, Livermore,
Poudre Park, Buckhorn Mountain, Mishawaka, Masonville, Carr,
Natural Fort, Laporte, Waverly, Owl Canyon and Buckeye.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
